<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851T.00/55: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Dakar (<persName type="to">Flexer</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-03">December 3,
                                        1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>127. Your 478, November 23 and 481, November 25.<note n="94" xml:id="d470fn94">Latter not printed.</note> Department desires
                                you to reopen office at once. You will of course appreciate <pb facs="0478" n="472" xml:id="pg_472"/> the necessity of the
                                Consulate functioning smoothly at this time. You should make every
                                effort to adjust locally any problems or difficulties which may have
                                arisen as to your position during the last few weeks, and to
                                maintain satisfactory relations with the constituted authorities of
                                French West Africa.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>